==Description==

The [[Templater_AuxView|Templater AuxView]] tool adds an auxiliary view to the active TechDraw drawing page based on a straight line in an already existing base view. This line, together with the Z-axis of the base view, defines the orientation of the auxiliary view. The end vertices of the line can either be selected separately or derived from a selected edge.

[[Image:TechDraw_AuxiliaryView_Pre02.png|300px]]

==Usage==

# Select two vertices or one edge in an existing view.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool.
# A new auxiliary view, an '''AuxView''' object, is created. Its line of sight is perpendicular to the line between the selected views.
# The '''Auxiliary view settings''' task panel opens.
#* Optionally change the marker of the view.
#* Optionally reverse the direction of the view.
#* Optionally align the direction with the line.
# Click {{Button|Ok}} to close the task panel and finish the tool.
# Drag the view and the annotation elements to their final positions. 

